Apple Inc. Completes iLife For iOS With Introduction Of iPhoto

Wednesday, 7 Mar 2012 02:18pm EST

Apple Inc. announced that it has introduced iPhoto for iPad and iPhone and updates to iMovie and GarageBand, completing its suite of iLife apps for iOS. iPhoto includes Multi-Touch features to sort photos and find shots, enhance and retouch images using fingertip brushes and share photo journals with iCloud. iMovie gives you the ability to create HD video on iPad and iPhone. GarageBand introduces Jam Session feature that allows a group of friends to wirelessly connect their iOS devices to play instruments and record live music together. The new iPad also features a 5 megapixel iSight camera.Â 

